        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> Libuscidi Victorini <expan><abbr>abunc</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <note>sic</note> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Cl</abbr><ex>audi</ex></expan> F<supplied reason="lost">or</supplied>tunati <expan><abbr>abunc</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <note>sic</note> maioris <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>ecimi</ex></expan> Satreni <expan><abbr>Cl</abbr><ex>audi</ex></expan> Satreniani <expan><abbr>eq</abbr><ex>uitis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>R</abbr><ex>omani</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Eugeni
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Dreieckige Interpunktion. P. Libuscidius Victorinus, Ti. Claudius Fortunatus erscheinen im Album der Dekurionen von Canosa 223, außerdem ein D. Satrenius Satrenianus, wohl der Vater des D. Satrenius Claudius Satrenianus. (C): nach AE 1984 alle Verstorbenen im Album bezeugt.</p>
            </div>
